'''Cedric Jan Itten''' (born 27 December 1996) is a Swiss professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[centre forward]] for German {{German football updater|FortunaD}} club [[Fortuna Düsseldorf]] and the [[Switzerland national football team|Switzerland national team]].

==Club career==

===Youth football===
Itten started his youth football with [[FC Black Stars Basel]] in 2003, before moving to [[BSC Old Boys]] a year later. In February 2007 he moved on to the youth department of [[Basel]] and played in their U-18 team and their U-21 team. Itten was a part of FC Basel's [[2013–14 UEFA Youth League]] campaign.

===Basel===
Itten signed a three-year junior professional contract on 21 August 2015 and joined Basel's first team for their [[2015–16 FC Basel season|2015–16 season]] under head coach [[Urs Fischer (footballer)|Urs Fischer]].<ref name="fcb-aktuell-2015/16-Itten">{{cite web | last = FC Basel 1893 | author-link = | date = 21 August 2015 | url = https://www.fcb.ch/aktuell/news/nachwuchs/2015/08/nachwuchs-profivertrag-fuer-u21-spieler-cedric-itten | title = Nachwuchs-Profivertrag für U21 Spieler Cedric Itten | format = | work = Junior professional contract for U21 player Cedric Itten | publisher = FC Basel 1893 AG | language = de | access-date = 16 November 2022}}</ref> After playing in two test games, Itten played his [[Swiss Super League|domestic league]] debut for the club in the home game in the [[St. Jakob-Park]] on 21 February 2016 as Basel won 5–1 against [[FC Vaduz|Vaduz]]. Itten played the assist as [[Birkir Bjarnason]] scored the last goal of the game.<ref name="fcb-achiv-2015/16">{{cite web | last = Verein "Basler Fussballarchiv” | author-link = | date = 21 February 2016 | url = https://www.fcb-archiv.ch/saison/spiele?command=detail&id=31045 | title = FC Basel - FC Vaduz 5:1 (0:1) | format = | publisher = Verein "Basler Fussballarchiv” | access-date = 16 November 2022}}</ref> He scored his first league goal for his club on 13 February in the away game in the [[Cornaredo Stadium|Cornaredo]] as Basel won 4–1 against [[FC Lugano|Lugano]]. It was the team's fourth goal, scored just before half time.<ref name="fcb-achiv-2015/16-Lugano-FCB">{{cite web | last = Verein "Basler Fussballarchiv” | author-link = | date = 13 February 2016 | url = https://www.fcb-archiv.ch/saison/spiele?command=detail&id=31047 | title = FC Lugano - FC Basel 1:4 (0:4) | format = | publisher = Verein "Basler Fussballarchiv” | access-date = 16 November 2022}}</ref> With the team Itten won the [[Swiss Super League]] championship at the end of the [[2015–16 Swiss Super League|2015–16 Super League season]]. For the club it was the seventh title in a row and their 19th championship title in total.<ref name="SRF-2015/16-19. Title">{{cite web | last = SRF | author-link = | date = 30 April 2016 | url = https://www.srf.ch/sport/fussball/super-league/fc-basel-holt-den-19-meistertitel | title = FC Basel holt den 19. Meistertitel | format = | work = FC Basel wins their 19th championship title | publisher = Schweizer Radio und Fernsehen (SRF) | language = de | access-date = 16 November 2022}}</ref>

====Luzern (loan)====
On 18 June 2016, Basel announced that they were loaning out Itten to [[FC Luzern]], until the end of the [[2016–17 Swiss Super League|2016–17 Swiss Super League season]], so that he could gain more first team playing experience.<ref name="fcb-aktuell-2016/17-Iten-Luzern">{{cite web | last = FC Basel 1893 | author-link = | date = 18 June 2016 | url = https://www.fcb.ch/aktuell/news/1-mannschaft/2016/06/itten-leihweise-zum-fc-luzern | title = Itten leihweise zum FC Luzern | format = | work = Itten on loan to FC Luzern | publisher = FC Basel 1893 AG | language = de | access-date = 16 November 2022}}</ref> Itten had a successful season scoring three goals in 28 appearances. Then, on 23 June 2017 Basel announced that they were prolonging their contract with Itten until 30 June 2020 and were continuing the loan Itten to Luzern for another period, until the end of the [[2017–18 Swiss Super League|2017–18 season]].<ref name="fcb-aktuell-2017/18-Iten-FCB-FCL">{{cite web | last = FC Basel 1893 | author-link = | date = 23 June 2017 | url = https://www.fcb.ch/aktuell/news/1-mannschaft/2017/07/der-fcb-verlaengert-den-vertrag-mit-cedric-itten | title = Der FCB verlängert den Vertrag mit Cedric Itten | format = | work = FCB extend Cedric Itten's contract | publisher = FC Basel 1893 AG | language = de | access-date = 16 November 2022}}</ref>

====Return to Basel====
Due to Basel's bad start to their [[2017–18 FC Basel season|2017–18 season]], due strikers transferring out and due to injuries of their replacements, on 13 September 2017 Basel announced that they had recalled striker Itten back from his loan.<ref name="fcb-aktuell-2017/18-Iten-FCL-FCB">{{cite web | last = FC Basel 1893 | author-link = | date = 13 September 2017 | url = https://www.fcb.ch/aktuell/news/1-mannschaft/2017/09/cedric-itten-zurueck-zum-fcb | title = Cedric Itten zurueck zum FCB | format = | work = Cedric Itten back to FCB | publisher = FC Basel 1893 AG | language = de | access-date = 16 November 2022}}</ref> His first goal following his return was the winning goal for the team in the [[Stadio Comunale (Chiasso)]] during the [[2017–18 Swiss Cup]] match on 17 September. It was the winning goal as Basel won 1–0 against [[FC Chiasso]].<ref name="fcb-achiv-2017/18-Cup-Chiasso-FCB">{{cite web | last = Verein "Basler Fussballarchiv” | author-link = | date = 17 September 2017 | url = https://www.fcb-archiv.ch/saison/spiele?command=detail&id=31281 | title = FC Chiasso - FC Basel 0:1 (0:0) | format = | publisher = Verein "Basler Fussballarchiv” | access-date = 16 November 2022}}</ref> Until the winter break Itten had 10 domestic league appearances, scoring two goals.

In January 2018 Itten was loaned to [[FC St. Gallen|St. Gallen]], but never returned to Basel.
During his period with the club, Itten played a total of 29 games for Basel scoring a total of five goals. 21 of these games were in the [[Swiss Super League]], three in the [[Swiss Cup]], two in the UEFA competitions (Champions League and Europa League) and three were friendly games. He scored three goals in the domestic league, one in the cup and the other was scored during the test games.<ref name="fcb-achiv-Cedric Itten">{{cite web | last = Verein "Basler Fussballarchiv” | authorlink = | year = 2022 | url = https://www.fcb-archiv.ch/spieler?command=detail&id=9311 | title = Cedric Itten - FCB statistic | format = | publisher = Verein "Basler Fussballarchiv” | accessdate = 16 November 2022}}</ref>

===St. Gallen===
On 17 January 2018, Basel announced that Itten would be loaned out to [[FC St. Gallen|St. Gallen]] until the end of the season, with an option to buy.<ref name="fcb-aktuell-2017/2018-Iten-FCB-FCSG">{{cite web | last = FC Basel 1893 | author-link = | date = 17 January 2018 | url = https://www.fcb.ch/aktuell/news/1-mannschaft/2018/01/cedric-itten-per-sofort-leihweise-zum-fc-st-gallen | title = Cedric Itten per sofort leihweise zum FC St. Gallen | format = | work = Cedric Itten is now on loan to FC St. Gallen | publisher = FC Basel 1893 AG | language = de | access-date = 16 November 2022}}</ref> On 29 June 2018 it was announced that St. Gallen pulled the option and had bought the striker.<ref name="SGN-St. Gallen-Itten-Langfristig">{{cite web | last = St. Galler Nachrichten | author-link =  | date = 29 June 2018 | url = https://www.st-galler-nachrichten.ch/sport/detail/article/cedric-itten-unterschreibt-langfristig-00144050/ | title = Cedric Itten unterschreibt langfristig | format =  | work = Cedric Itten signs long-term | publisher = St. Galler Nachrichten.ch | language = de | access-date = 16 November 2022 | archive-date = 21 November 2022 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20221121213752/https://www.st-galler-nachrichten.ch/sport/detail/article/cedric-itten-unterschreibt-langfristig-00144050/ | url-status = dead }}</ref>

===Rangers===
On 4 August 2020, Itten signed for Scottish club [[Rangers F.C.|Rangers]], on a four-year deal and for an undisclosed fee,<ref name="Roofe and Itten">{{ cite news | url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/53653208| title=Rangers sign Cedric Itten and Kemar Roofe on four-year deals | work=BBC Sport | publisher=BBC | date=4 August 2020}}</ref> reported to be £2.7 million.<ref>{{ cite news | url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/36621/12042399/rangers-sign-kemar-roofe-from-anderlecht-on-four-year-deal| title=Rangers sign Kemar Roofe from Anderlecht and Cedric Itten from St Gallen| publisher=Sky Sports | date=6 August 2020}}</ref> On 9 August 2020, Itten made his debut for Rangers in a [[Scottish Premiership]] match against [[St Mirren F.C.|St Mirren]].<ref>{{ cite news | url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/53626123 | title=Rangers 3-0 St Mirren | date=9 August 2020 | work=BBC Sport | publisher=BBC }}</ref>

On 27 September 2020, Itten scored his first two goals for Rangers, coming off the bench to score Rangers' fourth and fifth goals in a 5–1 win against [[Motherwell F.C.|Motherwell]] at [[Fir Park]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/54222424 |title=Motherwell 1-5 Rangers |date=27 September 2020 |publisher=BBC|access-date=28 September 2020}}</ref>

====Greuther Fürth (loan)====
On 31 August 2021, the last day of the 2021 summer [[transfer window]] Itten signed for German club [[SpVgg Greuther Fürth|Greuther Fürth]] on a season-long loan.<ref>{{cite news |title=Cedric Itten: Rangers striker joins Greuther Furth on loan |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/58398741 |access-date=31 August 2021 |work=BBC Sport |date=31 August 2021}}</ref> On 12 January 2022, Itten's loan was cut short as he was recalled by parent club [[Rangers F.C.|Rangers]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.rangers.co.uk/article/cedric-itten-returns-to-rangers-from-greuther-furth/7kD1GoUoeLa0vCAAinj40A |title=Cédric Itten returns to Rangers from Greuther Furth |publisher=Rangers FC |date=12 January 2022 |accessdate=12 January 2022}}</ref>

===Young Boys===
On 1 June 2022, his transfer to [[Bern]]ese club [[BSC Young Boys]] was announced.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.bscyb.ch/news?nID=13077|title=YB verpflichtet Cedric Itten |trans-title=YB buys Cedric Itten |publisher=[[BSC Young Boys]]|date=1 June 2022 |accessdate=1 June 2022}}</ref> He signed a four-year contract with the [[Swiss Super League]] club.

===Fortuna Düsseldorf===
On 28 July 2025, Itten signed with [[Fortuna Düsseldorf]] in German [[2. Bundesliga]].<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Fortuna Düsseldorf|url=https://www.f95.de/aktuell/news/profis/108/33924-cedric-itten-ist-ab-sofort-fortune/|title=Cedric Itten ist ab sofort Fortune|trans-title=Cedric Itten is now at Fortuna|date=28 July 2025|access-date=28 July 2025|language=de}}</ref>

==International career==
On 15 November 2019, Itten made his debut in the [[Switzerland national football team|Switzerland national team]], coming as a substitute in a 1–0 win over [[Georgia national football team|Georgia]] and scoring the only goal of the match.<ref>{{cite web |title=Switzerland 1-0 Georgia |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/50440486 |website=bbc.com |publisher=British Broadcasting Corporation |access-date=16 November 2019 |date=15 November 2019}}</ref> Three days later, he scored twice in a 6–1 win over [[Gibraltar national football team|Gibraltar]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Gibraltar 1-6 Switzerland |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/50467119 |website=bbc.com |publisher=British Broadcasting Corporation |access-date=19 November 2019 |date=18 November 2019}}</ref>

